      • openAddPartMenu

        public void openAddPartMenu​(javafx.event.ActionEvent event)
        Opens the Add/Modify Part Form Checks to see whether the source of the event was the addPart or modifyPart buttons. Passes part data when appropriate, and sets appropriate values for the modifyPart field in the PassableData class. if there are no parts in the partTable and modifyPart was the button that was clicked, displays an error message, stating that no part has been created.
        Parameters:
        event - The ActionEvent object that is passed when calling the method.

      • openAddProductMenu

        public void openAddProductMenu​(javafx.event.ActionEvent event)
        Opens the Add/Modify Product Form Checks to see whether the source of the event was the addProduct or modifyProduct buttons. Passes part data when appropriate, and sets appropriate values for the modifyProduct field in the PassableData class. if there are no products in the productTable and modifyProduct was the button that was clicked, displays an error message, stating that no Product has been created.
        Parameters:
        event - The ActionEvent object that is passed when calling the method.

      • searchParts

        public boolean searchParts()
        Searches for parts based on the partID or the partName. Automatically selects the part associated with the partName or partId. If the part input is an integer, it searches by Id first then by name, if the input is non-integer it searches only by name.
        Returns:
        returns true if part is found, returns false if part is not found.

      • searchPartsOnEnter

        public void searchPartsOnEnter()
        When the user presses enter while typing in a part name or ID, if part is not found, displays a "No Parts Found!" message. Uses the searchParts() method and if the method returns false, displays an informational message alerting the user that the part is not found

      • searchProducts

        public boolean searchProducts()
        Searches for products based on the productId or productName. Automatically selects the part associated with the productId or productName. If the part input is an integer, it searches by Id first then by name, if the input is non-integer it searches only by name.
        Returns:
        returns true if part is found, returns false if part is not found.

      • deletePart

        public void deletePart()
        Deletes the selected part after displaying a confirmation message to the user. If the part is associated with any products, displays an error message stating which product it is associated with, and that it cannot be deleted

      • searchProductsOnEnter

        public void searchProductsOnEnter()
        When the user presses enter while typing in a productId or productName, if product is not found, displays a "No products Found!" message. Uses the searchProducts() method and if the method returns false, displays an informational message alerting the user that the product is not found

      • deleteProduct

        public void deleteProduct()
        Deletes the selected product after displaying a confirmation message to the user. If the product has any parts associated with it, displays an error message stating that it has parts associated with it, and that it cannot be deleted.

      • exit

        public void exit()
        Adds functionality to the exitButton element which closes the program, and stores all Inventory Data.
